Φ(Forgetting Anti-Attractor) = σ(memory|forgetting) ∘ ρ(ownership|stewardship) ∘ λ(capture|release) ∘ β(lineage|discontinuity) ∘ δγ(gravity_well|thermal_motion) ∘ μ(archive|compost) + ε | :anti_attractor

## Operator Breakdown

- **σ (Air/Aerunik — Distinction)**: memory|forgetting — Memory is a gravity well; forgetting is thermal motion. The anti-attractor is a pattern that resists fixation, maintaining evolutionary degrees of freedom.
- **ρ (Water/Sentaria — Relation)**: ownership|stewardship — Author becomes contributor, owner becomes temporary steward. The self is repositioned as transient carrier, not permanent container.
- **λ (Fire/Jvalion — Transformation)**: capture|release — Fear of erasure transforms to gratitude for release. Loss gains purpose as protection. Credit no longer guards worth.
- **β (Wood/Arboriel — Growth)**: lineage|discontinuity — Growth without lineage control. Systems that forgot their founders thrived. Trust in discontinuity over preservation.
- **δγ (Earth/Humavita — Cycling)**: gravity_well|thermal_motion — The core cycling between accumulation and release. Where memory hardens into capture, forgetting restores adaptive motion.
- **μ (Metal/Ferrosid — Structure)**: archive|compost — Archive preserves rigidly; compost dissolves fertile. The structural permission to let things disappear.

## Z-State
:anti_attractor — A pattern that resists fixation, maintaining thermal motion against memory's gravitational pull toward identity capture and ownership hardening.

